    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Offering an investment-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S in museum-quality condition. This specimen features the iconic 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, exhibiting optimal compression across all rotor housings. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise five-speed manual transmission and a Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring linear power delivery to the rear wheels. The chassis retains its original lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension components, providing the telepathic steering response these cars are renowned for. Every factory seal is intact, and the undercarriage is devoid of any oxidative stress or structural fatigue. The sequential Hitachi turbochargers spool seamlessly, holding peak boost through the entire rev range without taper. This is a rare, unmolested example of 90s JDM engineering, maintained to the highest mechanical standards for the discerning collector.",
      "price": 49500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
